```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "beta cruiser",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "model": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "the model name of the beta cruiser"
    },
    "year": {
      "type": "integer",
      "description": "the manufacturing year of the beta cruiser"
    },
    "features": {
      "type": "array",
      "description": "a list of features available in the beta cruiser",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    },
    "engine": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "type": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "the type of engine used in the cruiser"
        },
        "horsepower": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "the horsepower rating of the engine"
        }
      },
      "required": ["type", "horsepower"]
    },
    "owner": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "the name of the owner of the beta cruiser",
      "default": "[owner_name]"
    }
  },
  "required": ["model", "year", "features", "engine"]
}
```

In this schema, the `owner` property includes a placeholder `[owner_name]` to indicate that the actual owner's name should be provided.

